Auto
Schedule follow-up prompts after Codex completes work or on a timer.

Usage:
$auto on-complete [options] (<message> | --last-user-message|-l)
$auto on-complete --round-robin "msg 1" "msg 2" ...
$auto every [options] (<interval|cron> <prompt> | --last-user-message|-l <interval|cron>)
$auto list
$auto show <runtime-id>
$auto pause <runtime-id>
$auto resume <runtime-id>
$auto rm <runtime-id>

Options:
--scope <session|repo|global>
--times <count>
--until <HH:MM>
--now
--policy '<command>'

Examples:
$auto on-complete continue working on this
$auto every 30m run tests
$auto pause session:auto-1
